{
  "stem": "15115.6",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When I came to this country here, they had iceboxes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, they didn't have fridges yet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was-- the guy used to sell a cube of ice box to put in the-- to put in the iceboxes, in 1948.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they were still selling bread with a horse and wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It used to come in the houses, and same way with the milk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we were-- we got adapted.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I got adapted very well, into Canadian life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so did all my friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All my friends did that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm happy every day I get up in the morning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm very happy to get up in the morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To me, it's an extra life-- that I got an extra life ahead of me, because as far as I'm concerned, I could have been in the gas chamber in 1943, on April 5.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Secondly if I wouldn't be lucky in concentration camp, I would have been dead, because I could not take the labor or the cold weather that we had, and the miserable things that we went through at the lager.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, if I wouldn't be lucky there, then I wouldn't be alive today.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as far as I'm concerned, I have a second life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every day that I am here-- we call it, in Polish, [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A [POLISH] means an extra portion of food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When we used to be in concentration camp, on a Wednesday they used to give us, let's say-- or a Thursday-- an extra piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in Auschwitz-- in Birkenau, was strictly Polish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] he says, tonight we have a [POLISH], which is an extra piece of bread they were giving us to eat.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But to me, [POLISH] means an extra life.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
